Description.val: The Material Handling Equipment (MHE) - A roll-up line that funds the replacement and service life extension of Material Handling Equipment which includes forklifts, cranes, and container handlers.  The replacement/service life extension program has been developed on an 'as required' basis.  This roll-up line includes funding for the  Backhoe Loader, Excavator Attachments, Hydroseeder, Hydraulic Excavator, Extended Boom Forklift, Light Rough Terrain Forklift (LRTF), Rough Terrain Container Handler,  and the Light Capability Rough Terrain Crane (7.5 ton).

Justification.val:
FY11 Base Appropriation $24.251M:
FY11 Base funding supports procurement of the Light Rough Terrain Forklift (LRTF), Extended Boom Forklift (EBFL), and the Hydraulic Excavator (HYEX).

FY11 Overseas Contigency Operations (OCO) $58.264M:
FY11 OCO funding supports procurement of the LRTF, Rough Terrain Container Handler (RTCH), and Hydroseeders.

FY12 Base Appropriation Request $37.055M: Funds the procurement of the Light Tactical Forklift (LTF).  The primary differences from the LRTF include an interchangeable armored and standard cab, climate control, rifle mount and personal protective gear storage space.

FY 12 Overseas Contingency Operations Request (OCO) $42.553M: Funds the procurement of Light Tactical Forklifts required to replace combat losses.

FY2013 Base Appropriation Request $20.659M: Funds the procurement of the Light Tactical Forklift (LTF) and begins the procurement of the Next Generation Extended Boom Forklift.  The primary differences from the EBFL include an interchangeable armored and standard cab, climate control, rifle mount and personal protective gear storage space.

FY 13 Overseas Contingency Operations Request (OCO) $19.100M: Funds the procurement of Light Tactical Forklifts and Extended Boom Forklifts required to replace combat losses.
